@page "/admin/privacy"

<PageTitle>HIP Privacy & Safety</PageTitle>

<section class="hip-page-heading compact">
    <div>
        <h1>Privacy & Safety</h1>
        <p>How HIP handles data, and how users stay in control.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="hip-privacy-callout">
    <strong>HIP is built privacy-first</strong>
    <p>HIP scans metadata and risk patterns, not the contents of personal conversations. HIP must never train AI models on private messages by default.</p>
</section>

<section class="hip-two-column">
    <article class="hip-panel padded">
        <h2>What HIP Collects</h2>
        <ul class="hip-check-list">
            <li>Message risk scores, not full message text</li>
            <li>Sender reputation signals</li>
            <li>Link scan results</li>
            <li>Platform connection metadata</li>
            <li>Rule trigger counts</li>
            <li>Privacy-safe scan history</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="hip-panel padded">
        <h2>What HIP Never Collects</h2>
        <ul class="hip-x-list">
            <li>Full private message content</li>
            <li>Contacts list</li>
            <li>Login credentials</li>
            <li>Payment information</li>
            <li>Private keys or signatures</li>
            <li>Location data</li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>

<section class="hip-panel padded narrow">
    <div class="hip-panel-heading flush">
        <div>
            <h2>Local-Only Mode</h2>
            <p>Process scans locally without sending data to HIP servers. Requires a future HIP desktop client.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="hip-toggle disabled"></span>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="hip-panel padded narrow">
    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>Normal risky findings target roughly 90 days of retention. Confirmed dangerous patterns can be retained longer. User-linked or private data should use the shortest practical retention period.</p>
</section>
